snippet.textDisplay: This is Kalasha Language which is spoken in Kalash Valley (District Chitral-Pakistan) and the same language is also spoken in Waigal Valley (Nuristan Province-Afghanistan. Kalasha language is from the Dardic family of the Indo-Aryan branch. Kalash are a Dardic indigenous people and are considered to be Pakistan’s smallest ethnoreligious community with unique culture, language and follow a form of ancient Hinduism. They live in District Chitral(Pakistan) in 3 valleys like Bumburet, Rumbur & Birir and in Afghanistan, they live in Nuristan Province, Afghanistan.
